```php
<?php
// https://github.com/weirdan/doctrine-psalm-plugin/blob/master/stubs/EntityManagerInterface.phpstub

namespace Doctrine\ORM;

interface EntityManagerInterface
{
    /**
     * @param class-string<T> $entityName
     * @param mixed           $id
     *
     * @return T|null
     *
     * @template T
     */
    public function getReference(string $entityName, $id);
}

// https://github.com/weirdan/doctrine-psalm-plugin/blob/master/stubs/EntityManager.phpstub

namespace Doctrine\ORM;

class EntityManager implements EntityManagerInterface
{
    /**
     * @template T
     * @param class-string<T> $entityName
     * @param mixed           $id
     *
     * @return null|T
     */
    public function getReference($entityName, $id)
    {
    }
}

namespace NS;
// https://github.com/weirdan/doctrine-psalm-plugin/blob/229a38f68991551bef48d5262b4d2ae2dd5785ab/tests/acceptance/EntityManager.feature#L83
      use Doctrine\ORM\EntityRepository;
      use Doctrine\ORM\EntityManager;
      interface I {}
      /**
       * @psalm-suppress InvalidReturnType
       * @return EntityManager
       */
      function em() {}


      /** @psalm-trace $_z */
      $_z = em()->getReference(I::class, 1);
```

```
Psalm output (using commit a174b4c):

INFO: Trace - 50:7 - $_z: NS\I|null
```
</details>

So I spent quite a while trying to debug this, but wasn't able to fix the issue. `TemplateResult::$upper_bounds` does not contain an entry for the inherited template, but the type has it as an intersection, so the replacement is not happening for the intersected (inherited) template.

I also couldn't produce a proper test for it. Something strange is going on here.

@muglug do you have any pointers on how I can track this down?
